## Documentation Blockers

- RECAST 00 artifacts were missing from `/opt/Axodus/.instructions` at audit start. RECAST 01 created the active maturity framework under coordinator-approved execution.
- Missing nucleus `STATUS.md` files: ACS, Academy, Business, Dex, Lottery, Marketplace, Mining, Trading.
- Documentation nucleus `STATUS.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, `WORKFLOW.md`, `SECURITY.md`, and recovery support files were created in REQ-02 as L4-candidate evidence; final L4 remains blocked by VitePress asset inventory/alignment, publication authority, versioning path, and asset inventory.
- Lottery `.instructions/TASKS.md` appears inconsistent and may contain Security-oriented content; it needs a future documentation hygiene pass.
- DEX has no `STATUS.md`; REQUEST 04 closeout and 04O/04P backlog status must remain documented through existing task/roadmap/report files until a STATUS recovery task is approved.

## Validation Blockers

- No builds, tests, installs, or technical validation commands were run during RECAST 01 by design.
- Academy, Marketplace, Mining, Business, Lottery, BBA-Agency, Documentation, and several other nuclei need current validation reports before their maturity can be raised.
- AxodusAPP has prior recovered build/test evidence, but real-data integration remains unvalidated.
- Governance has prior recovered backend validation and static contract planning evidence, but production persistence/indexing/query transport implementation remains blocked.
- Trading local E2E was previously recovered, but current audit did not rerun it and live/paper runtime expansion remains forbidden.

## Mock/Local Blockers

- Mock/local evidence does not authorize production execution.
- Business, Mining, Lottery, Defi, Governance, AxodusAPP, DEX registry, and Trading all rely on local/mock/read-only or paper-only boundaries for current evidence.
- Any transition from mock/local to real integration requires an explicit request, validation plan, and security/governance gate.

## App Visibility Blockers

- AxodusAPP is the integration shell, but module visibility is uneven across nuclei.
- Academy, Marketplace, Mining, Business, Lottery, ACS, and Governance have evidence of AxodusAPP visibility or routes, but not all have current nucleus `STATUS.md` baselines.
- DEX interface work remains read-only/backlog; routing/swap preview/settlement execution is disabled.

## Contract/Interface Blockers

- Governance API Transport Track is BACKLOG CONTROLLED. No new HTTP routes/controllers or AxodusAPP real backend client are approved.
- Core is pre-RC and not an execution authority; Governance/ACS consumer pilot reviews remain incomplete.
- DEX registry contracts and route metadata are non-executing and fixture-only; no live token-list, pool, route, or provider data is approved.
- Defi Phase 3 contracts/adapter/custody implementation remains not approved.
- Business persistence/repository contracts require validation before persistence implementation.

## Integration Blockers

- No nucleus is L6 as an overall portfolio baseline.
- Cross-nucleus real integration remains gated behind portfolio allocation.
- AxodusAPP real Governance HTTP integration is blocked until backend transport contract tests, transport implementation approval, response envelope stability, and CORS/dev origin policy approval.
- Trading real exchange integration, credential vault runtime, production database usage, withdrawals, and treasury movement remain blocked.
- ACS must not bypass Governance/Core authority boundaries.

## Production/Execution Blockers

The following are globally forbidden unless separately approved with governance, security, audit, deployment, rollback, and operations evidence:

- real fund movement;
- treasury withdrawal or treasury movement;
- live trading;
- paper/live trading runtime expansion without explicit approval;
- CEX execution or withdrawal;
- DEX swap execution;
- route execution or hidden route providers;
- settlement execution;
- marketplace minting or value-bearing asset transfer;
- lottery prize, payout, randomness, or gambling-sensitive execution;
- mining payout execution;
- production wallet signing;
- production private keys;
- production RPC secrets;
- production database usage for execution-sensitive flows;
- on-chain writes;
- token-list silent approval;
- unrealistic financial claims, guaranteed APY, or yield promises.

## Repository/Versioning Blockers

- Root `/opt/Axodus` is not a Git repository; global docs are workspace-local and cannot be committed from root.
- Global Docs / Instructions lacks a formal Git versioning decision and remains the top structural recovery item for PORTFOLIO SPRINT 01.
- Global docs are workspace-local and not formally versioned.
- Global docs versioning strategy requires coordinator decision.
- Repository restructuring is forbidden without explicit approval.
- Global docs cannot claim production readiness.
- Decision Pending: select official versioning home for global Axodus instructions.
- Trading is `dev...origin/dev [ahead 1]`; preserve existing local changes.
- BBA-Agency instructions versioning appears resolved for `.instructions/BUB_AGENTS.md`; `git check-ignore -v .instructions/BUB_AGENTS.md` produced no ignore match during this audit.
- Untracked `.instructions/BUB_AGENTS.md` files were reported in Core, Documentation, Governance, AxodusAPP, Defi, ACS, Business, Lottery, and Mining; future commits must be handled per repository and must not overwrite unrelated local work.
- Linked/vendor repositories, DEX forks, token-list repos, and generated artifacts remain protected from cleanup/reset/normalization without explicit approval.

